From: lemoer <git@irrelefant.net>
Date: Fri, 5 Jun 2026 16:49:41 +0000
Subject: fix: properly detect lan3/4 on fb7360 (and probably other fritzboxes)

The issue is theoretically present up to the current mainline linux
kernel and no fix is yet there. However, due to good luck and boot
timing, the issue doesn't seem to occurr in OpenWrt 25.12 currently
during the normal boot. It is still existing though and can be
triggered by manually reloading the lantiq_gswip kernel module.

As it currently seems, a proper upstream patch needs more work. So,
we apply this fix here, since it also works.

Link: https://github.com/openwrt/openwrt/issues/20629
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/netdev/20260520151355.1371163-1-leo.moerlein@proton.me/T/#u

